{
 "name": "RPlog_Calling_in_on_Old_Friends",
 "title": "Calling in on Old Friends",
 "summary": "At a crowded starport on Dac, the smuggler Shael is overseeing the unloading of medical supplies she has contracted to deliver for the New Republic when she runs into her old acquaintance Rasi, fresh from a tense admiralty meeting about the planet's fate. The two catch up warily; Rasi senses something is wrong and presses Shael, who reluctantly admits she spent time in an Imperial labor camp but deflects the details. Over drinks in the starport cantina, Rasi recruits her to help uncover how weapons are being smuggled past the blockade to the Quarren insurgency, handing her a list of secondary contacts and warning her how to approach them carefully. An IGN broadcast revealing Imperial backing for the Quarren rebels interrupts them, sharpening Rasi's priorities toward plugging the smuggling routes. They part with Shael promising to report anything she learns, and her asking eagerly for permission to visit her friend Kyrin aboard the Audacity, betraying a quiet, almost desperate need to reconnect.",
